@startuml technology-sequence-event-persistence-snapshot-replay-escalation-v1
title Event Persistence, Snapshot, Replay, and Escalation (Operational Sequence)

participant "LangGraph Orchestrator\nAPP-016" as APP_016
participant "PM Agent\nAPP-007" as APP_007
participant "CSCO Agent\nAPP-015" as APP_015
database "EventStore\nAPP-001" as APP_001
participant "Local File and Process Service\nTSV-001" as TSV_001
participant "DashboardServer\nAPP-020" as APP_020

APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(specialist.completed, invocation_id)
APP_016 -> APP_001: check_snapshot_interval()
alt threshold reached
  APP_016 -> APP_001: create_snapshot("periodic")
else gate passed or sprint close
  APP_016 -> APP_001: create_snapshot("gate.evaluated|sprint.close")
end

APP_016 -> APP_001: replay_from_latest_snapshot() [restart/resume]
APP_001 --> APP_016: workflow state + trigger sequence

APP_016 -> APP_007: request gate decision context
APP_016 -> APP_015: request safety vote
alt vote timeout/unavailable
  APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(algedonic.escalated, reason="safety-vote-timeout", correlation_id)
  APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(phase.suspended, correlation_id)
else vote available
  APP_015 -> APP_001: record_event(decision.recorded, correlation_id)
end

APP_020 -> APP_001: query events + snapshot metadata for observability views
TSV_001 -> APP_001: persist snapshot artifacts on local filesystem path

note right of APP_001
Operational observability is read from APP-001,
while fail-safe escalation remains correlation-linked
and replay-safe across restart/resume cycles.
end note
@enduml
